(Atho Binary Build and Pinning Guide) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Date: 2026-04-18) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(This document defines the production binary layout, build flow, and pinning controls for Atho) Tj
T*
(native components. The goal is deterministic runtime loading with explicit integrity checks,) Tj
T*
(while keeping build and deployment workflows straightforward for operators.) Tj
T*
(- Canonical Binary Layout) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(All runtime binaries are loaded from:) Tj
T*
(- Binaries/<platform-tag>/) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Typical platform-tag examples include architecture and OS identity \(for example, macOS arm64 vs) Tj
T*
(Linux x86_64\). Runtime should not depend on ad-hoc source-tree paths.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Common binary artifacts:) Tj
T*
(- falcon_cli\(.exe\)) Tj
T*
(- libatho_falcon_verify.\(dylib|so|dll\)) Tj
T*
(- libtx_signing_body_bridge.\(dylib|so|dll\)) Tj
T*
(- libutxo_batch_check.\(dylib|so|dll\)) Tj
T*
(- libatho_pow_cpu.\(dylib|so|dll\)) Tj
T*
(- gpu_miner_opencl\(.exe\)) Tj
T*
(- gpu_miner_cuda\(.exe\) when CUDA build is available) Tj
T*
(- Pin Registry and Metadata) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Integrity metadata is maintained in:) Tj
T*
(- Binaries/pin_registry.json) Tj
T*
(- Binaries/<platform-tag>/binary_meta.json) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(These files map expected SHA3-384 digests to binary names and are consumed by runtime pin) Tj
T*
(validators. If a binary is rebuilt and metadata is not refreshed, strict mode will reject the) Tj
T*
(load.) Tj
T*
(- Strict Loading Mode) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Enable strict canonical-path loading with:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Behavior in strict mode:) Tj
T*
(- runtime only loads from canonical Binaries/<platform-tag>/ paths,) Tj
T*
(- legacy fallback paths are disabled,) Tj
T*
(- hash mismatches fail closed.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(This is the recommended production setting.) Tj
T*
