T*
(- Security and Policy Context) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Binary integrity controls complement consensus policy but do not replace consensus validation.) Tj
T*
(Active policy values remain independent:) Tj
T*
(- block target 120s, retarget 180,) Tj
T*
(- tx confirmations 6, private tx confirmations 6, coinbase maturity 150,) Tj
T*
(- fee floor 1 atom/vB, minimum tx fee 500 atoms.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Binary pinning protects runtime execution integrity; consensus rules protect chain validity.) Tj
T*
(- Recommended Production Standard) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Use this baseline in all production-like environments:) Tj
T*
(- canonical binary paths only,) Tj
T*
(- strict mode enabled,) Tj
T*
(- deterministic build logs retained,) Tj
T*
(- pin registry/version control updates reviewed,) Tj
T*
(- release checksums signed and externally verifiable.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Following this standard reduces upgrade risk and makes binary-level audit trails clear for) Tj
T*
(operators and security reviewers.) Tj
T*
